name: Luna
description:
"Gemini" from the "Luna" collection by Nushin is now available on hic et nunc.

"Gemini" is a 3500x3500px image which is done by color pencil on A4 paper. 

the "Gemini" 's idea came from the Nebula itself; Gemini is one of the constellations of the zodiac and is located in the northern celestial hemisphere. It was one of the 48 constellations described by the 2nd century AD astronomer Ptolemy, and it remains one of the 88 modern constellations today. Its name is Latin for twins, and it is associated with the twins Castor and Pollux in Greek mythology. Its symbol is ♊︎ (Unicode ♊).
